 client", "recommendations/0/date": "July 20, 2015", "recommendations/0/description": "The individual development training by Frederic Borgoltz of TheCoach was an enriching professional encounter. Aside from the information that I got during the six-month sessions, it had challenged me with innovations and brought new perspective to my leadership approach and style. Anyone who is keen to experience it, I would say that it is not the standard executive coaching. It is informal, interactive and fun like a fitness for the mind for the ‘A’ players. ", "recommendations/0/name": "Frédéric Borgoltz", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Junior Retiree", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/frédéric-borgoltz-7697723/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAACljMEBsft9XssFr00da-uCSAugh1uaiKg", "skills/0/title": "Data Analysis", "skills/1/title": "Financial Analysis", "skills/2/title": "Business Analysis", "skills/3/title": "Accounting", "skills/4/title": "Advertising", "skills/5/title": "Administration", "skills/6/title": "Strategy", "skills/7/title": "Negotiation", "skills/8/title": "Capital Expenditures", "skills/9/title": "Operations", "skills/10/title": "Performance Appraisal", "skills/11/title": "Interpersonal Skills", "skills/12/title": "Revenue & Profit Growth", "skills/13/title": "Operational Excellence", "skills/14/title": "Data Privacy", "skills/15/title": "P&L Management", "skills/16/title": "Succession Planning", "skills/17/title": "Service Standards", "skills/18/title": "Quality Control", "skills/19/title": "Key Performance Indicators", "totalExperienceYears": "20.6", "totalRecommendationsGiven": "1", "totalRecommendationsReceived": "0", "urn": "ACoAAAD3MHIBKL4Qi7f9I8ipNw6K-AmvLZen-MQ", "volunteerAndAwards/0/description": "Located in the slum district of Bangkok in Klong Toey, the Foundation provides care and education for children aged from four months to five years old. These children come from low income families, and many suffer from neglect, malnutrition and abuse. \n\nThe project started in January 2012 by sponsoring lunch meals, donating funds to improve its facilities, providing school learning materials and volunteering a day to play with the children. The visitation/charity work is done on a quarterly basis.\n\nIt is interesting for me to share one of our activities that manifest this commitment not only as a leader of my team but also on a personal basis. In August of 2012, a memorable experience was sharing a full day, interacting with the slum children of the foundation. Together with my staff, the project included putting into order the charity shop, repairing the children’s tables and chairs, enhancing the garden, playground and facilities of the premises. Personally it was overwhelming and fun to visit and share smiles with these children.\n", "volunteerAndAwards/0/duration/months": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/duration/years": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/end_date/month": "9", "volunteerAndAwards/0/end_date/year": "2020", "volunteerAndAwards/0/industry": "Children", "volunteerAndAwards/0/is_current_position": "false", "volunteerAndAwards/0/organization": "Foundation of Slum Child Care", "volunteerAndAwards/0/role": "Volunteer", "volunteerAndAwards/0/start_date/month": "1", "volunteerAndAwards/0/start_date/year": "2012", "volunteerAndAwards/1/description": "Located in Rajathevee, Bangkok, the foundation was founded in 1939. It is the first foundation in Thailand for the blind and visually impaired children. The foundation accepts all girls and boys. The curriculum starts from kindergarten until Grade 6. During junior and senior high school years, since 1997 students have been required to attend the integrated program with regular schools.\n\nIn 2013, as part of our ongoing Corporate Social Responsibility, we added the Foundation for the Blind to our endeavors to support the Kingdom’s community development. Beginning January, different groups (combination of management and staff) visited the foundation on monthly basis. The project included:\n\n1 Donating calendars and cards to produce teaching and learning materials like braille books \n2 Creating learning tools for reading with the blind students’ fingers \n3 Gate refurbishing\n4 Sponsoring special lunch \n\nOne of the personal experiences with the blind students was a day on 26 December 2013. Together with the other Chatrium Hotels & Residences properties in Bangkok, I led the Emporium Suites by Chatrium to sponsor a Christmas/New Year special lunch for all the blind students. In return the students demonstrated to us their full potential in sports and singing/dancing activities. On a personal basis, through this worthy deed of sharing happiness to people that due to different circumstances could not have as comfortable life as the one I was born with, it turned out that I took and leaned much more that I gave.\n", "volunteerAndAwards/1/duration/months": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/1/duration/years": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/1/end_date/month": "12", "volunteerAndAwards/1/end_date/year": "2020", "volunteerAndAwards/1/industry": "Education", "volunteerAndAwards/1/is_current_position": "false", "volunteerAndAwards/1/organization": "Foundation for the Blind in Thailand", "volunteerAndAwards/1/role": "Volunteer", "volunteerAndAwards/1/start_date/month": "1", "volunteerAndAwards/1/start_date/year": "2013"}$$::jsonb),
